# Current Wealth - Destitute
Wealth Level / 01 Destitute					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Destitute			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTDestitute			DESC:You're stone broke, usually hungry, and hopelessly ill-equipped. At the GM's option you may own a single item of value, such as your old sword, an heirloom. or some item of unknown properties. Typical equipment here includes rusty, worn knives, tattered clothing, improvised padded armor, and other rubbish.																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.184
Wealth Level Perk / Armor, Shields, and Weapons		KEY:Wealth Template ~ Destitute Equipment		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTDestitute																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.184				BENEFIT:Even if pristine to start with, any armor, shields, or weapons you pick up will shortly be in horrible shape. Half AC bonus from armor and shields (minimum +1 apiece), weapons get -2 to hit and damage.
Wealth Level Perk / Magical Items				KEY:Wealth Template ~ Destitute Magic		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTDestitute																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.184				BENEFIT:You might possess a single charm, provided that something weird is going on.
Wealth Level Perk / Mounts, Pets, and Familiars		KEY:Wealth Template ~ Destitute Companions	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTDestitute																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.184				BENEFIT:Any mount you can lay your hands on gets -5 move, one-half normal HP, and a -3 on all rolls. As far as pets and familiars go, you could probably manage a rat or something.
Wealth Level Perk / Recognition				KEY:Wealth Template ~ Destitute Recognition	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTDestitute																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.184				BENEFIT:Even people who know you are likely to pretend they don't. Anyone at this wealth level gains a +2 circumstance modifier to Disguise and Knowledge: Local.
Wealth Level Perk / Training					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Destitute Training		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTDestitute																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.184				BENEFIT:Training: +2 Skill points per level gained at this wealth rank in any of skills listed above; -2 on any two chosen attributes due to illness/hunger exposure/ etc while the character remains at this wealth level.

# Current Wealth - Poor
Wealth Level / 02 Poor						KEY:Wealth Template ~ Poor				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTPoor				DESC:It's no feast - but you usually get enough to eat, sleep relatively warm, and can feed the kids. There isn't much to spare, and sadly enough, the vast majority of humanity has subsisted at this level throughout history. Almost any kind of job, or acting as casual labor, supports this level of wealth, as will minor criminal activities																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.185
Wealth Level Perk / Armor, Shields, and Weapons		KEY:Wealth Template ~ Poor Equipment		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTPoor																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.185				BENEFIT:There really isn't any money to spare for this; staves, slings, clubs, improvised spears, and work knives, are about the limit. You can usually get someone to make up a crude suit of padded armor for you. Your best bet is to try to join the militia; that'll get you some basic gear, such as leather armor, spear, shortsword, small wooden shield, and a few javelins along with the training to use them effectively.
Wealth Level Perk / Magical Items				KEY:Wealth Template ~ Poor Magic			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTPoor																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.185				BENEFIT:One minor, and usually utilitarian, charm. Fire- and light- stones, healing charms, minor enhanced tools, and other handy items are the most common.
Wealth Level Perk / Mounts, Pets And Familiars		KEY:Wealth Template ~ Poor Companions		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTPoor																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.185				BENEFIT:Any animals you have are going to either be common, inexpensive working beasts or sources of food. Ferrets are useful, if a bit pungent. A pack-ox or horse is possible, a real mount is unlikely.
Wealth Level Perk / Acquaintances				KEY:Wealth Template ~ Poor Aquaintances		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTPoor																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.185				BENEFIT:Guildmembers, past employers, and possibly a few members of the local underworld. If you really need an assistant, you may be able to manage an apprentice, impressionable kid, or one of your relatives.
Wealth Level Perk / Training					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Poor Training			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTPoor																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.185				BENEFIT:Any character who levels while at this wealth level gains +2 SP to be spent on Profession, Craft, Bluff, or Gather Information, but it's rare for an adventurer to spend much time at this level.

# Current Wealth - Common
Wealth Level / 03 Common					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Common				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTCommon				DESC:You live decently, and can even afford a bit of education, a few books, a larger family, and good tools. If you decide to "go adventuring" you can afford basic equipment, although usually not an especially wide assortment of it. This is the most common default starting point for characters from the lower classes, implying a reasonably successful career as a craftsman, lesser crook, farmer, guard, or whatever.																																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.186
Wealth Level Perk / Armor, Shields, and Weaponry	KEY:Wealth Template ~ Common Equipment		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTCommon																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.186				BENEFIT:You can afford light armor, shields, common, inexpensive, weapons (shortswords, short bows, javelins, etc) and equipment of ordinary quality.
Wealth Level Perk / Magical Items				KEY:Wealth Template ~ Common Magic			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTCommon																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.186				BENEFIT:Normally three minor "charms." At least at first, these will usually be utilitarian, but the definition of "utilitarian" can vary a good deal depending on the character's background.
Wealth Level Perk / Mounts, Pets, and Familiars		KEY:Wealth Template ~ Common Companions		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTCommon																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.186				BENEFIT:You can obtain common animals, a light riding horse (likely a bit long in the tooth, but serviceable) and a healthy mutt to act as a guard dog. "Noble" animals, including hawks, purebred hounds, hunting cats, warhorses and exotic imports, are still out of reach.
Wealth Level Perk / Retainers					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Common Retainers		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTCommon																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.186				BENEFIT:You may have a house- or errand-boy and know an old woman or man who purports to be a witch. For the most part you won't know anyone the least bit important.
Wealth Level Perk / Training					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Common Training		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTCommon																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.186				BENEFIT:Any character who levels while at this wealth level gains no special benefits, and suffers no unusual penalties.

# Current Wealth - Well Off
Wealth Level / 04 Well Off					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Well Off			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWellOff				DESC:You're doing pretty well, at least for a normal crafter or small businessman, younger son, petty noble, very prosperous farmer, minor trader, caravan master, or minor governmental official. You're quite unlikely to be especially influential, but you probably know people who are. A reasonably successful mercenary, minor specialist, respectable priest, or starting-off upper class adventurer, will usually fall into this category.																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.186
Wealth Level Perk / Armor, Shields, and Weapons		KEY:Wealth Template ~ Well Off Equipment		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWellOff																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.186				BENEFIT:You can afford full plate armor, exotic weapons, longbows and specialized equipment. Still, at least for the time, masterwork equipment remains out of reach.
Wealth Level Perk / Magical Items				KEY:Wealth Template ~ Well Off Magic		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWellOff																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.186				BENEFIT:Three charms and one talisman.
Wealth Level Perk / Mounts, Pets, and Familiars		KEY:Wealth Template ~ Well Off Companions		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWellOff																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.186				BENEFIT:You can afford high quality common animals, trained warhorses, and so on. Exotic imports are still simply too expensive.
Wealth Level Perk / Retainers					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Well Off Retainers		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWellOff																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.186				BENEFIT:You may have a single extremely loyal assistant, guard, or henchman, connections with assorted skilled professionals in various fields and a dozen or so ordinary employees. While these usually won't be going on adventures, they make life a lot easier most of the time.
Wealth Level Perk / Training					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Well Off Training		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWellOff																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.186				BENEFIT:Any character who levels while at this wealth level gains no special benefits, and suffers no unusual penalties.

# Current Wealth - Affluent
Wealth Level / 05 Affluent					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Affluent			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTAffluent			DESC:You're a midlevel noble, colonial governor, run a sizable business, guild, or great estate, are backed by a king, have rifled some notable treasure hordes, have backing from a extraplanar entity, or are a supported member of a major court. A manor, several houses, mystical tower, splendid apartments, or fine mansion is probably in order.																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.187
Wealth Level Perk / Armor, Shields, and Weapons		KEY:Wealth Template ~ Affluent Equipment		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTAffluent																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.187				BENEFIT:Are all treated as being "masterwork." The character can readily afford to buy specialized equipment from high-quality crafters.
Wealth Level Perk / Legal Privileges			KEY:Wealth Template ~ Affluent Legal		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTAffluent																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.187				BENEFIT:Characters at this level enjoy a good deal of leeway about things like the use of deadly force against an "attacker," carrying armor, shields, and weapons, or riding in the city streets, and will virtually always get the benefit of the doubt unless the other side is even richer. It's also almost impossible to drive you insane; you're usually limited to eccentric.
Wealth Level Perk / Mounts, Pets, and Familiars		KEY:Wealth Template ~ Affluent Companions		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTAffluent																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.187				BENEFIT:You can afford exotic pets, like fine hawks and rare imported animals. Trained warbeasts, chargers, and packtrains are at your disposal.
Wealth Level Perk / Magical Items				KEY:Wealth Template ~ Affluent Magic		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTAffluent																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.187				BENEFIT:Five charms and two talismans.
Wealth Level Perk / Retainers					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Affluent Retainers		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTAffluent																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.187				BENEFIT:You may have a couple of competent and loyal guards and assistants, possibly connections with an eccentric hedge wizard or minor priest (these are often related to you, and prone to sending you on odd missions or having weird visions), and quite a few employees and general gofers.
Wealth Level Perk / Skill Bonuses				KEY:Wealth Template ~ Affluent Skill Bonuses	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTAffluent																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.187				BENEFIT:Characters who level at this wealth level gain an extra skill point each time.

# Current Wealth - Wealthy
Wealth Level / 06 Wealthy					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy				DESC:You're filthy rich. You can afford hundreds of servants, field a private army, live in a palace or castle, and have a notable spellcaster on call. Similar benefits apply to those supported by dukes, minor kings, major organizations, and to those who loot the treasures of ancient empires.																																																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.187
Wealth Level Perk / Armor/Shields				KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Equipment		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																														BONUS:COMBAT|AC|2|TYPE=Armor.STACK|PREEQUIP:1,TYPE=Armor,TYPE=ArmorType	BONUS:COMBAT|AC|2|TYPE=Shield.STACK|PREEQUIP:1,TYPE=Shield																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.187				BENEFIT:Treat armor as one category lighter for movement and special ability purposes. This applies to shields as far as proficiencies go. Add a +2 Wealth AC bonus to shields and armor and improve the Armor Check Penalty (if any) by 2.
Wealth Level Perk / Legal Privileges			KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Legal			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.187				BENEFIT:At this point you're virtually above the law; having the resources to fund private armies tends to have that effect. Those with grievances usually resort to outlaw tactics or even larger armies.
Wealth Level Perk / Magical Items				KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Magic			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.187				BENEFIT:Seven charms and three talismans.
Wealth Level Perk / Mounts, Pets, and Familiars		KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Companions		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.187				BENEFIT:Mounts gain 2d4 levels of Magical Beast, +1d3 to each attribute, and +5' to Move. Pets and Familiars gain 1d4 levels of Magical Beast, +1d2 to each attribute, and +5' to Move.
Wealth Level Perk / Recognition				KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Recognition		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.187				BENEFIT:Anyone at this level of wealth will be widely known, influential in the community and often "on call." With power comes authority - and a great deal of responsibility unless the character opts to become a hermit.
Wealth Level Perk / Retainers					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Retainers		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.187				BENEFIT:You often have a hedge wizard or minor priest, a sage or scholar (if desired), some bodyguards and agents, and an assortment of craftsmen and ordinary employees numbering up to the hundreds at this level. Standard d20, you may have a dozen wizards.
Wealth Level Perk / Skill Bonuses				KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Skill			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																																																								BONUS:SKILL|Diplomacy,Gather Information,Intimidate|2																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.187				BENEFIT:+2 nameless bonus to Diplomacy, Gather Information, and Intimidate, thanks to the use of cash and high-quality gear. Masterwork tools and reference material (for knowledge-based skills) is presumed wherever it is useful.
Wealth Level Perk / Training					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Training		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.187				BENEFIT:Superb. You gain +2 SP and +1 HP per level gained while this template applies, and a +2 to any single attribute (total, not per level).
Wealth Level Perk / Weapons					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Wealthy Weapons		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTWealthy																																																																																																																														BONUS:COMBAT|TOHIT|2|TYPE=Wealth	BONUS:COMBAT|TOHIT.Unarmed|-2|TYPE=Wealth																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.187				BENEFIT:Your weaponry gains +2 built-in Wealth bonuses. It may be made of adamantine, silver, or of exotic materials as desired. Wealth bonuses stack with magical enhancement.

# Current Wealth - Imperial
Wealth Level / 07 Imperial					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Imperial			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTImperial			DESC:You're richer than many kings. You can afford to rebuild kingdoms, fund crusades, dispatch agents to the far corners of the world, grant great boons, and erect massive monuments. Seizing the horde of a legendary dragon, control of a mighty kingdom, the direct backing of a god, or some combination of similar events, will raise someone to this level.																																																																																																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.188
Wealth Level Perk / Armor/Shields				KEY:Wealth Template ~ Imperial Equipment		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTImperial																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.188				BENEFIT:Treat as one category lighter for movement and special ability purposes, half the usual weight, with +3 AC Wealth bonus, and -3 on Armor Check Penalty (if any).
Wealth Level Perk / Magical Items				KEY:Wealth Template ~ Imperial Magic		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTImperial																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.188				BENEFIT:Seven charms and three talismans.
Wealth Level Perk / Mounts, Pets, and Familiars		KEY:Wealth Template ~ Imperial Companions		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTImperial																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.188				BENEFIT:Mounts gain 3d4 levels of Magical Beast, +1d4 to each attribute, and +10' to Move. Pets and Familiars gain 1d4+2 levels of Magical Beast, +1d3 to each attribute, and +10' to Move.
Wealth Level Perk / Recognition				KEY:Wealth Template ~ Imperial Recognition	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTImperial																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.188				BENEFIT:You will be widely recognized and will have a lot of calls on your time. Adventurers will be expected to deal with major menaces, organize the defense of the realm, and similar things. You're above the law.
Wealth Level Perk / Retainers					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Imperial Retainers		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTImperial																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.188				BENEFIT:You gain a competent mage, a skilled priest, and superb scholars and advisors, as well as an assortment of "special agents," accountants, servants, skilled craftsmen, bodyguards, and ordinary employees. This presumes that powerful spellcasters are relatively rare. In many d20 worlds you may command the services of whole academies of mages and temples full of clerics.
Wealth Level Perk / Skill Bonuses				KEY:Wealth Template ~ Imperial Skill		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTImperial																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.188				BENEFIT:You gain a +4 Wealth bonus to Diplomacy, Gather Information, and Intimidate, thanks to the ready availability of cash and the finest gear. You are assumed to have masterwork equipment whenever it would help you (and you have equipment at all), including superb reference works for knowledge-based skills.
Wealth Level Perk / Training					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Imperial Training		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTImperial																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.188				BENEFIT:The finest. +2 SP and +2 HP per level gained while this template applies. The character also gains a +2 wealth bonus to any one attribute while at this wealth level and a +10%% experience bonus.
Wealth Level Perk / Weapons					KEY:Wealth Template ~ Imperial Weapons		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.WTImperial																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.188				BENEFIT:All your weaponry gains a +4 innate Wealth bonus and may be made of adamantine, silver, or exotic materials as you desire.


