Arcanum Minimus / Ambient Magic			KEY:Arcanum Minimus ~ Ambient Magic			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.ArcanumMinimusFeatChoice								DESC:Conventionally used to power cantrips and trivial talismans, ambient magical energy is freely available, but very weak. The casting time increases greatly - from free actions to actions, from actions to minutes, and from minutes to hours. Ambient magic cannot power spells that normally require more than ten minutes to cast.																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.126
Arcanum Minimus / Catalyst Materials		KEY:Arcanum Minimus ~ Catalyst Materials		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.ArcanumMinimusFeatChoice								DESC:The magical forces which lie within certain materials selected by the game master (a vampire's fang, the dust from a dragon's eggshell, ogre magi blood, odd minerals and rare earths, magical woods, certain crystals, etc), may be tapped to power magic. Sadly, such materials are difficult to acquire and are only good for a limited number of castings of particular spells before their power is exhausted.																																																																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.126
Arcanum Minimus / Powers of Chaos			KEY:Arcanum Minimus ~ Powers of Chaos		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.ArcanumMinimusFeatChoice								DESC:Calling on the powers of Chaos to aid you is straightforward, but reckless. The caster must save against his or her own spell (use Will if no save is specified): On a "1", it goes drastically wrong and produces a wild magical effect rather than what you want. On a failure, or a "2" in any case, it is somewhat distorted or has strange side effects (treat as a secondary spell of up to one-half of the original spell's power level).																																																																																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.126
Arcanum Minimus / Life Energy				KEY:Arcanum Minimus ~ Life Energy			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.ArcanumMinimusFeatChoice								DESC:One of the most common sources of extra energy for spells, but also one of the least friendly, this technique draws out the internal strength of the caster. Spellcasters using this energy source may draw on their own life force, either saving against their own spell (Will if no save is listed) to avoid fatigue (doing this twice causes the exhausted state as usual) or expending HP (usually Spell Level/2 d6), XP (5 per spell level), or temporary attribute drain (usually 1d4) in the spellcasting. Ruthless mages may draw on the life energy of sacrifices (small animals and large plants will suffice for low-level spells; a ninth level spell might require multiple sentient beings), or on the surrounding environment. Using this option reduces soil and vegetation to lifeless ash in a radius of roughly 3 feet per level of the spell, a condition that may persist for lengthy periods. This is definitely an evil act and is unpopular with everything dependent on the land.																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.126
Arcanum Minimus / Magical Devices			KEY:Arcanum Minimus ~ Magical Devices		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.ArcanumMinimusFeatChoice								DESC:The energies stored within charged, or "uses-per-day", magical items may provide power for compatible spells. Simply enough, this depletes one charge or use per spell. Certain items, such as the Rod of Wonder, are compatible with almost any spell. The GM must rule on compatibility for other items. In general, a similar effect or descriptor is compatible.																																																																																																																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.126
Arcanum Minimus / Powers of Darkness		KEY:Arcanum Minimus ~ Powers of Darkness		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.ArcanumMinimusFeatChoice								DESC:The forces of corruption are always ready to supply quick and easy power - for a price. Black magic slowly twists and warps thosewho use it, leaving a taint that's difficult to purge away. This is represented by an accumulating Corruption score. Calling on black magic normally results in 1d4 points of corruption. When your corruption score exceeds your current Will save (plus constant bonuses) plus your stage of descent you must make a Will save (DC 13 if you've been using your magic for good purposes, 16 if you've been using it for a general tool, 21 if you've been using it for selfish or evil purposes) or descend a step into the power of evil. On a success, the mage has resisted the temptations of the powers of darkness. In either case, the corruption score resets to zero. Barring such a dramatic resolution, a character's corruption score falls by one point a week automatically, by one point a day via penance, rituals, or meditation in a holy place, and by 1d4 points whenever the character makes a great commitment to good or a major sacrifice in its pursuit.																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.126
Arcanum Minimus / Powers of Light			KEY:Arcanum Minimus ~ Powers of Light		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.ArcanumMinimusFeatChoice								DESC:The powers of light are stern and demanding masters, as pure and terrible as the fires of the sun. The price of drawing upon such power is purity of purpose, mind, and spirit: being a sword to stand against the darkness. This is hell on your social life. Unfortunately, unless a character lives up to very high standards, his or her spells start fizzling as the powers that be, whatever they are, decline to help him or her out. Optionally, similar benefits can be derived from the Lords of Order, but such entities issue endless orders and directives. Few mortals care to call on them.																																																																																																																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.126
Arcanum Minimus / Karmic Debts			KEY:Arcanum Minimus ~ Karmic Debts			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.ArcanumMinimusFeatChoice								DESC:Calling on supernatural beings to help you out has one basic flaw: they tend to want you to return the favor, and are powerful enough to enforce such a debt. While they rarely call upon low level characters, truly powerful individuals make truly useful pawns. Karmic debts are unlikely to be a problem at first, but lead to many unanticipated adventures later. As a variation, a character might be linked with some sort of minor entity, which the caster must keep happy if he or she wishes to continue using such spells. In either case, the karmic creditor sends irresistible curses if the character refuses to pay up.																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.126
Arcanum Minimus / Reduced Power			KEY:Arcanum Minimus ~ Reduced Power			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.ArcanumMinimusFeatChoice								DESC:This isn't actually a power source; it's what happens when a spell is cast without building up the power to do it properly, usually due to failure to fulfill other conditions from this list. Spells suffer a -2 on the DC of saving against them and a -4 on the effective caster level per "missing" condition. Factors such as duration and range are reduced as the game master wishes. A few very high-level mages may not care ("So who cares if it only goes off at L12? It maxes out at 10!"), but lesser magi need every scrap of power they can muster.																																																																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.126
Arcanum Minimus / Special Conditions		KEY:Arcanum Minimus ~ Special Conditions		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.ArcanumMinimusFeatChoice								DESC:The spell is more restricted than usual. It may require peculiar environmental conditions (e.g., moonlight), that the caster possess special knowledge or skills (such as a target's "True Name" or an extensive knowledge of biophysics), won't affect certain targets, and so on. In general, this is a catch-all category. On the other hand, if the limitation doesn't really limit the spell, it certainly doesn't count. A Fireball which only affects enemies is improved, not restricted. In general, mages shouldn't make a habit of using many of these; special conditions should be closely tied to the character concept or an integral part of very special spells. Optionally, the game master may permit spells to gain up to a -3 level modifier from special conditions, provided that they are both extremely specific (e.g. only during the great once-a-century conjunction at the Gate of Ebon while holding the Scepter of Night) and have been built into the spell formula.																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.126

