Harvest of Artifice / Alchemic Mastery		KEY:Harvest of Artifice ~ Alchemic Mastery	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.HarvestOfArtificeFeatChoice								DESC:You may distill the XP you harvest into alchemical compounds. These function as universal power components, storing those XP for later use by anyone. Unfortunately, this is only 50%% efficient.																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.131
Harvest of Artifice / Gleaning			KEY:Harvest of Artifice ~ Gleaning			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.HarvestOfArtificeFeatChoice								DESC:You may gather an extra 50 XP per month. This option may be taken repeatedly.																																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.131
Harvest of Artifice / Philosopher's Stone		KEY:Harvest of Artifice ~ Philosopher's Stone	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.HarvestOfArtificeFeatChoice								DESC:This application requires both Alchemic Mastery and Transmutation. It allows both effects to be stored in an alchemical talisman, to be used at the option of the possessor. In the case of Transmutation, the holder of the item can use it to transmute materials even without possessing this feat.																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.131
Harvest of Artifice / Transmutation			KEY:Harvest of Artifice ~ Transmutation		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.HarvestOfArtificeFeatChoice								DESC:You may infuse XP into material to transmute it into more useful forms. This costs 1 XP per 2 GP worth of equipment so produced.																																																																																																																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.131

